        <span class="hedonic-heading">HEDONIC</span>
        <br/>
        <br/>
        Invariably, there are many factors determining when, what, and how much we eat. Our lab is investigating these underlined factors
        by first considering the neural circuit - the functional connections and pathways between brain regions - that control appetite and satiety.
        <br/>
        <br/>
        The hypothalamus, located at the base of the brain, is a vital brain region for the control of body weight and food intake.
        We are evaluating hypothalamic connectivity with the forebrain, midbrain, and hindbrain
        to determine how brain communication signals appetite and satiety. Furthermore, we are also evaluating which chemical messengers
        enable this communication.
        To do this, we are studying the interactions between endogenous hormones and neurotransmitters by applying <em>ex vivo</em> electrophysiology
        and optogenetics to behavioral or transgenic mouse models.
